    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-12-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-12-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="493"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d493">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. No. 763.72112/5741</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Saloniki</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HG1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Horton</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 6, 1917</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your November 22. War Trade Board advises your question is covered by fact that
                    Trading with Enemy Act applies to allies of enemy and that liability American
                    firms in regard existing contracts would be determined by Greek laws but their
                    liability cannot affect policy of War Trade Board.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
